WEBVTT

00:01.898 --> 00:04.280
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:21.090 --> 00:28.614
♪♪

00:28.649 --> 00:30.271
Why do we have to do it
in person?

00:30.306 --> 00:31.893
Can't we just pay
the cable bill online?

00:31.928 --> 00:34.413
No, because our Internet
has been cut off.

00:34.448 --> 00:35.932
Haven't you noticed
how weird the kids

00:35.966 --> 00:37.071
have been acting lately?

00:37.106 --> 00:38.279
[ Sad music plays ]

00:38.314 --> 00:40.040
[ Clicking, computer beeping ]

00:40.074 --> 00:41.110
Memes.

00:41.144 --> 00:42.318
Fails.

00:42.352 --> 00:43.491
Kittens.

00:43.526 --> 00:44.872
Aw, give them time.

00:44.906 --> 00:47.357
I'm sure they'll discover
all the good things IRL.

00:47.392 --> 00:49.221
You know,
all the hashtag good things

00:49.256 --> 00:50.602
that aren't
on the Internet.

00:50.636 --> 00:52.638
If you feel me,
smash the like button below.

00:52.673 --> 00:53.846
What are you
talking about?

00:53.881 --> 00:56.573
You know, all the good
things, like...

00:57.678 --> 01:00.094
Really? You can't think of
anything important to you

01:00.129 --> 01:01.475
that's not
on the Internet?

01:01.509 --> 01:02.855
Something you've built
your life around,

01:02.890 --> 01:04.478
giving you constant
emotional support

01:04.512 --> 01:06.100
and joy through the years?

01:06.135 --> 01:07.446
Hmm-mnh.

01:07.481 --> 01:09.552
I'll give you a clue.
It begins with "F."

01:09.586 --> 01:10.898
[ Gasps ]
Foo--

01:10.932 --> 01:12.417
Family.

01:12.451 --> 01:13.383
Seamless.

01:13.418 --> 01:15.109
Yeah.
Nice save, honey.

01:15.144 --> 01:17.560
Now, you just stay here in the
car while I go pay this bill.

01:17.594 --> 01:18.906
[ Video game chiming ]

01:18.940 --> 01:20.597
[ Chuckles ] Excuse me.
I'd like to pay this --

01:20.632 --> 01:22.323
Eh.

01:22.358 --> 01:23.807
Yo?
Yeah, hi.

01:23.842 --> 01:25.602
I'd like to pay
this bill, please.

01:25.637 --> 01:28.053
In person?
Yes, in person.

01:28.088 --> 01:30.538
Not online?
No, in person.

01:30.573 --> 01:31.746
Eh.
Hey, Tony.

01:31.781 --> 01:33.886
We got a dinosaur
out here.

01:33.921 --> 01:35.060
What, dinosaur?!

01:35.095 --> 01:35.888
Where is it?
Where is it?

01:35.923 --> 01:36.889
No, no, no, Tony.

01:36.924 --> 01:38.477
I mean like
an old-fashioned person.

01:38.512 --> 01:40.514
Oh, thank goodness.
Don't do that!

01:40.548 --> 01:42.550
[ Sobbing ] You know
I'm scared of dinosaurs!

01:42.585 --> 01:44.276
I-I'm sorry, man.

01:44.311 --> 01:45.519
Excuse me.

01:45.553 --> 01:47.141
Not to interrupt
whatever this is,

01:47.176 --> 01:48.556
but where can I
pay this?

01:48.591 --> 01:50.317
Fourth floor,
they can help you there.

01:50.351 --> 01:52.388
Thank you.I am so sorry.

01:52.422 --> 01:53.251
Just don't!

01:53.285 --> 01:58.048
[ Loud rumbling ]

01:59.602 --> 02:02.639
Sir, could you keep your
sound system down, please?

02:02.674 --> 02:04.538
That's my stomach,
Officer.

02:04.572 --> 02:06.022
I'm so hungry.

02:06.056 --> 02:08.921
In fact, I'm so hungry
I think I'm hallucinating.

02:12.132 --> 02:14.548
Wow, that was pointless.
You're already a hot dog.

02:14.582 --> 02:16.066
For your information,
the preferred term

02:16.101 --> 02:18.862
is "artificially flavored
reconstituted meat snack."

02:18.897 --> 02:24.592
I suggest you get
something to eat, sir.

02:24.627 --> 02:26.180
A vending machine, eh?

02:26.215 --> 02:28.700
Why not pop inside and get
yourself something tasty, hmm?

02:28.734 --> 02:31.323
But I don't work there.Just bluff it out.

02:31.358 --> 02:32.566
Act as if
you own the place,

02:32.600 --> 02:33.981
and nobody will
dare question you.

02:34.015 --> 02:36.777
But Nicole said I had
to wait in the car.

02:36.811 --> 02:37.985
Hmm.

02:38.019 --> 02:39.538
Why are you
always like this?

02:39.573 --> 02:41.195
Maybe you should sort
out your own issues

02:41.230 --> 02:42.507
before advising
other people.

02:42.541 --> 02:44.405
Aw, give it a rest,
Goody Two-shoes.

02:44.440 --> 02:46.269
Why don't you ever try
to see things my way?

02:46.304 --> 02:47.650
Hmm.

02:47.684 --> 02:49.238
You don't have to
listen to that guy.

02:49.272 --> 02:50.342
Why not teach him a lesson?

02:50.377 --> 02:51.412
Who are you calling...

02:51.447 --> 02:53.483
[ Chatter ]

02:53.518 --> 02:56.003
I either need
some food or some therapy.

02:56.037 --> 02:57.384
Eh, chips are cheaper.

02:57.418 --> 02:58.661
[ Telephone ringing ]

02:58.695 --> 03:00.318
[ Coin clanking, light thud ]

03:00.352 --> 03:02.389
Hmm, hmm.

03:02.423 --> 03:03.355
Excuse me, sir.

03:03.390 --> 03:04.908
Do you have an appointment?

03:04.943 --> 03:06.289
Uh...

03:06.324 --> 03:07.428
Just act like
you own the place.

03:07.463 --> 03:09.568
I mean, where's
the harm in that?

03:09.603 --> 03:11.052
Eh, just do
what he says.

03:11.087 --> 03:11.881
I'm hungry.

03:11.915 --> 03:12.951
Uh, sir?

03:12.985 --> 03:16.265
[ Gulp! ]
I don't need an appointment.

03:16.299 --> 03:18.094
I own the place.

03:18.128 --> 03:19.854
I'm sorry
for keeping you waiting, sir.

03:19.889 --> 03:22.409
Please don't fire me.
I'll tell the CEO immediately.

03:22.443 --> 03:23.720
♪♪

03:23.755 --> 03:25.308
♪ He's back
-♪ He's back?!

03:25.343 --> 03:26.689
♪ I'll tell him right away

03:26.723 --> 03:28.277
♪ He's back
-♪ He's back?

03:28.311 --> 03:29.761
♪ A monumentous day

03:29.795 --> 03:31.245
♪ Send somebody
down to greet him ♪

03:31.280 --> 03:33.937
♪ Who'd have thought
I'd finally meet him? ♪

03:33.972 --> 03:35.629
♪ He's back ♪ Who's back?

03:35.663 --> 03:37.217
♪ The founder of this place

03:37.251 --> 03:38.528
♪ Agog
♪ Aghast

03:38.563 --> 03:40.392
♪ But no one's
ever seen his face ♪

03:40.427 --> 03:41.807
♪ He's a genius of business

03:41.842 --> 03:43.740
♪ Is there no limit
to his wizness? ♪

03:43.775 --> 03:46.191
It's pronounced
"wiseness."

03:46.226 --> 03:47.503
♪ You're back I'm back?

03:47.537 --> 03:49.436
♪ Will you please
accept this gift? ♪

03:49.470 --> 03:50.816
♪ May I say, sir,
you're my hero ♪

03:50.851 --> 03:52.266
♪ To have built this up
from zero ♪

03:52.301 --> 03:53.854
♪ John, stop acting
like a bootlick ♪

03:53.888 --> 03:56.684
♪ May I offer, Sir,
a toothpick? ♪

03:56.719 --> 03:58.686
♪ He's back

03:58.721 --> 03:59.825
Uh...

03:59.860 --> 04:01.275
♪ Here's accounts
and acquisitions ♪

04:01.310 --> 04:02.932
♪ Asset strippers ♪ Statisticians

04:02.966 --> 04:04.278
Who can help me
pay this bill?

04:04.313 --> 04:06.349
Try level seven.
Ask for Phil.

04:06.384 --> 04:07.764
What's that awful
stench of evil?

04:07.799 --> 04:10.146
Could be marketing.
Or legal.

04:10.180 --> 04:12.148
♪ They say he crushes
rivals under foot ♪

04:12.182 --> 04:13.736
♪ Stripped departments,
raised output ♪

04:13.770 --> 04:15.151
♪ Dare not look him
in the eyes ♪

04:15.185 --> 04:16.601
♪ He's sure to cut
you down to size ♪

04:16.635 --> 04:18.016
♪ I'm nervous,
apprehensive ♪

04:18.050 --> 04:19.569
♪ Quick, which tie
looks more expensive? ♪

04:19.604 --> 04:21.122
♪ I heard he's a giant
amongst giants ♪

04:21.157 --> 04:22.779
♪ Six foot six
of raw defiance ♪

04:22.814 --> 04:24.194
♪ I heard short
and quite abusive ♪

04:24.229 --> 04:25.817
♪ Who can say?
He's so reclusive ♪

04:25.851 --> 04:27.128
♪ All fall silent
at the ding ♪

04:27.163 --> 04:28.716
♪ What fresh vision
will he bring? ♪

04:28.751 --> 04:30.856
♪ Sharing wisdom,
insight, knack ♪

04:30.891 --> 04:32.548
[ Ding! ]

04:32.582 --> 04:34.550
Welcome, Founder.
You are back.

04:34.584 --> 04:35.758
[ Music ends ]

04:35.792 --> 04:37.760
[ Gulp! ]
Yes.

04:37.794 --> 04:41.142
I don't think
that's him.

04:41.177 --> 04:42.005
[ Buzz! ]

04:42.040 --> 04:43.421
Aah!Of course it's him.

04:43.455 --> 04:44.801
What are the odds
someone would show up

04:44.836 --> 04:46.251
pretending to be the founder
on the exact day

04:46.286 --> 04:49.944
we invited him to approve
the new office design?

04:49.979 --> 04:52.844
Uh, yeah, is that guy
going to be okay?

04:52.878 --> 04:54.984
Do you want him to be okay?

04:55.018 --> 04:56.675
Yes?

04:56.710 --> 04:59.057
Hello, Linda, there's a guy
coming down to reception.

04:59.091 --> 05:00.921
He's already landed?
[ Inhales sharply ]

05:00.955 --> 05:02.957
Well, sweep him up
and pay his medical bills.

05:02.992 --> 05:04.718
[ Chuckling ]
He's going to be fine.

05:04.752 --> 05:06.064
Anyway, thanks for coming.

05:06.098 --> 05:07.583
We know you're
nominally reclusive,

05:07.617 --> 05:08.894
never leave the house,
and, frankly,

05:08.929 --> 05:10.275
we thought you'd been dead
for years,

05:10.310 --> 05:12.277
but we're glad you're here.
Now, as you know,

05:12.312 --> 05:15.798
we hired the most expensive
architect money could buy.

05:15.832 --> 05:17.351
I tell you, I haven't
seen so many zeroes

05:17.386 --> 05:19.560
since I walked through economy
to get to first class.

05:19.595 --> 05:20.630
Am I right?

05:20.665 --> 05:22.149
All: Ha ha ha-ha!
We're rich!

05:22.183 --> 05:24.393
I must warn you, his designs
are pretty cutting-edge,

05:24.427 --> 05:25.670
but we know you're
used to thinking

05:25.704 --> 05:27.188
outside the current aesthetic.

05:27.223 --> 05:29.708
Yeah, well, I know
a long word, too.

05:33.367 --> 05:35.369
Spaghetti.He's a genius.

05:35.404 --> 05:39.166
Okay. So allow me to present
the bold new future of Chanax.

05:39.200 --> 05:40.547
I love it.

05:40.581 --> 05:41.720
Don't you want me
to take off the --

05:41.755 --> 05:43.757
No! It's perfect
as it is.

05:43.791 --> 05:45.759
Of course. Why didn't
we see it before?

05:45.793 --> 05:47.588
The long, sleek columns,
the wheel motifs,

05:47.623 --> 05:49.901
the bold silhouette,
it's genius.

05:49.935 --> 05:52.593
Well, it certainly taps
into the zeitgeist.

05:52.628 --> 05:54.802
Exactly, like a ghost
on stilts.

05:54.837 --> 05:56.632
That's what I said,
"A ghost on stilts."

05:56.666 --> 05:58.599
Nothing says business
like a ghost on stilts.

05:58.634 --> 06:01.222
We'll get construction
started right away.

06:01.257 --> 06:02.638
Sir, if I may say,

06:02.672 --> 06:04.294
for too long this company
has been held back

06:04.329 --> 06:07.297
by mama's boys,
vegetarians, and yes-men.

06:07.332 --> 06:08.816
Am I right?
All: Yes!

06:08.851 --> 06:10.611
What we need now
is exactly your kind

06:10.646 --> 06:11.923
of out-of-the-box thinking.

06:11.957 --> 06:13.925
Forget throwing
caution to the wind.

06:13.959 --> 06:16.341
You take caution out
for a lovely five-course meal,

06:16.376 --> 06:17.653
meet caution's parents,

06:17.687 --> 06:19.206
then skip out the bathroom
window during dessert,

06:19.240 --> 06:20.380
leaving caution's dad,

06:20.414 --> 06:21.933
who didn't like you
in the first place,

06:21.967 --> 06:23.210
to pick up the tab
while you circle around

06:23.244 --> 06:24.798
and set fire to
caution's beach house.

06:24.832 --> 06:26.247
Am I right?
Yes!

06:26.282 --> 06:27.732
So come on.

06:27.766 --> 06:29.527
I'm sure you have many more
bold, seat-of-the-pants,

06:29.561 --> 06:32.392
pull-off-your-own-kneecaps-and
-run-them-up-the-flagpole ideas

06:32.426 --> 06:33.427
to share with us.

06:33.462 --> 06:35.602
Uh, yeah.
I guess so.

06:35.636 --> 06:37.051
Yes. Yes, I do.

06:37.086 --> 06:39.053
[ Squeaking ]

06:39.088 --> 06:41.918
We should start by making
the floors less slippy.

06:43.092 --> 06:44.507
Dad: Hi.

06:44.542 --> 06:45.819
I'm sure you've noticed

06:45.853 --> 06:47.890
we've made a few changes
here at Chanax,

06:47.924 --> 06:49.374
and because we value
your opinion

06:49.409 --> 06:51.341
but don't want to talk
to you personally,

06:51.376 --> 06:54.379
I'll try and answer some of
your questions in this video.

06:54.414 --> 06:57.417
Since I've had my baby, can I
switch to more flexible hours?

06:57.451 --> 07:00.040
That's right.
The office chairs areboring.

07:00.074 --> 07:02.007
So we're replacing them
with an alternative

07:02.042 --> 07:04.251
that's a bit more fun
and works better.

07:04.285 --> 07:06.460
That's right.
We're putting the "fun"

07:06.495 --> 07:09.256
in functionality.

07:09.290 --> 07:10.671
Funfunctionality.

07:10.706 --> 07:12.639
[ Grunting ]

07:12.673 --> 07:14.019
Whoa!

07:14.054 --> 07:15.642
Will the recent changes
affect my pension?

07:15.676 --> 07:17.298
You can't work
when you're hungry.

07:17.333 --> 07:20.750
That's why we're installing a
pizza kiln at every workstation.

07:20.785 --> 07:22.718
It's too hot to work.

07:22.752 --> 07:25.065
What will happen
to my dental plan?

07:25.099 --> 07:27.792
Dad: [ Chuckles ] Exactly.
We've replaced all the stairs

07:27.826 --> 07:29.966
in the building
with slides and flumes.

07:30.001 --> 07:32.175
There's nothing there.
It is just a sheer drop.

07:32.210 --> 07:33.832
It'll be done
by the time this goes out.

07:33.867 --> 07:35.558
We'll cut it in later.
Just jump.

07:35.593 --> 07:36.456
Eh.

07:36.490 --> 07:38.250
Whee!

07:38.285 --> 07:39.597
Ow!

07:39.631 --> 07:40.701
Whee!

07:40.736 --> 07:42.082
Wow, that was
so funfunctional.

07:42.116 --> 07:44.015
It works a dream.
But what about me?

07:44.049 --> 07:45.395
I'm on a temporary contract.

07:45.430 --> 07:47.501
How will I be affected?And the office itself?

07:47.536 --> 07:50.642
Well, as part of our continuing
vision, we are redesigning,

07:50.677 --> 07:53.887
starting with totally removing
the structural foundations.

07:53.921 --> 07:55.958
[ Jackhammer hammering ]

07:55.992 --> 07:57.856
And we've got other
exciting innovations

07:57.891 --> 08:00.307
on the way, too,
like the double-kiln.

08:00.341 --> 08:01.722
What's with the ridiculous
new office furniture?

08:01.757 --> 08:02.585
Why aren't I allowed
to open...

08:02.620 --> 08:04.104
What about my dentist?

08:04.138 --> 08:06.209
Drilling out the
foundations ain't safe!

08:06.244 --> 08:09.489
Dad:
Chanax, "We're listening."

08:09.523 --> 08:11.007
Excuse me, Phil?

08:11.042 --> 08:12.561
I was sent here
to pay this bill.

08:12.595 --> 08:15.184
I've now been here longer
than some of the employees.

08:15.218 --> 08:17.324
-Hey, Nicole.
-Oh, hey, Al.

08:17.358 --> 08:18.394
How are the kids?

08:18.428 --> 08:20.085
Working hard
or hardly working, Jimbo?

08:20.120 --> 08:21.811
Jim: Yeah, ain't that
the truth?

08:21.846 --> 08:23.054
What's that?

08:23.088 --> 08:24.676
Oh, that's been
happening quite a lot.

08:24.711 --> 08:26.298
They're taking out
the foundations.

08:26.333 --> 08:28.542
That really doesn't
sound like a good idea.

08:28.577 --> 08:30.302
It beats
the triple kiln.

08:30.337 --> 08:31.890
[ Panting ]

08:31.925 --> 08:33.374
Can I just
get this paid?

08:33.409 --> 08:34.824
[ Crash! ]

08:34.859 --> 08:38.552
Yeah, the computer doesn't
seem to be responding.

08:38.587 --> 08:40.036
Give it a minute.
Right.

08:40.071 --> 08:42.452
I'm going to pay this bill
if it's the last thing I do.

08:42.487 --> 08:43.557
Where's your manager?

08:43.592 --> 08:45.835
Woman:
Ah, save yourselves!

08:45.870 --> 08:47.699
I think she
just stepped out.

08:47.734 --> 08:50.219
Then I'm taking this
all the way to the top.

08:50.253 --> 08:51.496
To the founder?

08:51.531 --> 08:52.946
If I have to.

08:54.464 --> 08:56.950
Come on. What's wrong
with the elevators?

08:56.984 --> 08:58.227
That's a new thing.

08:58.261 --> 09:00.332
You need two people
to work it.

09:02.093 --> 09:03.957
[ Rumbling, powering down ]

09:03.991 --> 09:05.579
Gah. What's this now?

09:05.614 --> 09:07.305
Wait for it.

09:07.339 --> 09:09.341
Elevator Voice:
You have requested
the top floor.

09:09.376 --> 09:12.448
Three. Two. One!

09:12.482 --> 09:13.760
What?

09:13.794 --> 09:16.763
You've got to dance
to make it go up.

09:16.797 --> 09:18.247
Perfect!

09:18.281 --> 09:19.869
Keep going!

09:19.904 --> 09:21.699
The whole building's
crumbling.

09:21.733 --> 09:23.770
The employees have
all been sent home.

09:23.804 --> 09:26.496
I see you
for what you are now.

09:26.531 --> 09:27.601
[ Gulp! ]

09:27.636 --> 09:30.500
A gosh-darned
marketing genius!

09:30.535 --> 09:31.709
Think of the publicity.

09:31.743 --> 09:33.158
We'll be all over
the front pages,

09:33.193 --> 09:35.954
and the sidewalk, but I get it.
It's like the Titanic.

09:35.989 --> 09:38.508
Crashing that boat made it
an international superstar.

09:38.543 --> 09:39.544
[ Rumbling ]

09:39.579 --> 09:43.617
♪♪

09:43.652 --> 09:48.415
[ Elegant music plays ]

09:48.449 --> 09:49.623
[ Ding! ]

09:49.658 --> 09:50.969
Come on.

09:51.004 --> 09:53.420
No, I'm staying
right here.
Why?

09:53.454 --> 09:57.389
I never knew what I wanted
to do with my life until now.

09:57.424 --> 09:58.667
You want to dance
in the elevator

09:58.701 --> 10:00.013
of a crumbling building?

10:00.047 --> 10:02.671
Oh, yeah. See you
at the Christmas party.

10:02.705 --> 10:03.637
[ Ding! ]

10:03.672 --> 10:05.881
[ Crashing ]

10:05.915 --> 10:07.641
Who's in charge, here?

10:07.676 --> 10:08.918
[ Chair squeaking ]

10:08.953 --> 10:10.299
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

10:10.333 --> 10:12.542
Richard?
What are you doing here?

10:12.577 --> 10:14.096
I have absolutely no idea.

10:14.130 --> 10:16.616
This is precisely why I tell you
to stay in the car.

10:16.650 --> 10:19.757
Wait a minute. You're not
the founder of Chanax?

10:19.791 --> 10:21.448
No, but you guys
seemed so convinced,

10:21.482 --> 10:23.553
I figured Imust be
in the wrong.

10:23.588 --> 10:24.762
What?
You're not a hard-nosed,

10:24.796 --> 10:26.487
no-nonsense
business guru at all.

10:26.522 --> 10:29.249
You're a lying, swindling,
talentless con artist,

10:29.283 --> 10:30.871
which is, hmm, you know,
po-tay-to, po-tah-to.

10:30.906 --> 10:32.114
[ Crashing ]

10:32.148 --> 10:34.116
[ Gasps ]
How do we get out of here?

10:34.150 --> 10:36.325
Well, we had a corporate helipad
put in right above us.

10:36.359 --> 10:38.672
-Oh, thank goodness.
-But thanks to this brainbox,

10:38.707 --> 10:40.950
we replaced it
with something funfunctional.

10:40.985 --> 10:42.469
[ Ice cream truck
music playing ]

10:42.503 --> 10:44.747
[ Crashing, music dying ]

10:44.782 --> 10:49.165
[ Crashing ]

10:49.200 --> 10:50.373
[ Car alarm blaring ]

10:50.408 --> 10:52.203
[ Coughs ]

10:52.237 --> 10:55.206
Ugh. So does that mean
